Results:
1Enriched culture gave an overall (vaginal and/or rectal) colonisation rate of 21% compared to 10% with standard culture.232% of women studied had at least one risk factor, most commonly prolonged rupture of membranes (49%).350% of women with any risk factor did not receive IAP (Table 1
).4Only 21% of GBS carriers received IAP, whilst 67% of women who received IAP were GBS-negative (Table 2
).5The baby colonisation rate was 8% (90/1125). Positive vaginal culture identified 78% of the positive babies; positive rectal culture 89% and both rectal and vaginal positive culture combined 93%.
